metadata.name: Beautiful Power
metadata.description:
"Where your voice can be heard, let them listen."

We casually think of Medusa as a monster; a head full of snakes and a gaze to turn anyone into stone.

And even though she's popularly referenced as a monster and rightfully feared, her tragic story reveals that  Medusa is more complex than we imagine.

She was renowned for her beauty,  and her power persisted even after death, but what can we learn from the ancient story of Medusa and her encounters with Perseus, Poseidon and Athena?

As an artist, one question I ask myself is, what must she have felt in those moments?

In "Beautiful Power" I imagine her misfortune but also her amusement; her sorrow but also her strength.
